HEADWORD: Intrinse
<hw>In*trinse"</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧n*tr⟦icr⟧ns")</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[See <er>Intrinsic</er>, and <er>Intense</er>.]</ety> <def>Tightly
drawn; or (perhaps) intricate.</def> <mark>[Very rare]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like rats, oft bite the holy cords atwain,⟦br⟧
Which are too <qex>intrinse</qex> to unloose.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intrinsic</ent>⟦br⟧
